instruction: How does a compass work?
output_1:
The Earth is a giant magnet. It has a magnetic field that reaches from the North Pole to the South Pole. The magnetic field is created by the rotation of the Earth and is strongest near the poles and weaker as you move farther away. The magnetic field is tilted at about 11 degrees to the Earth's rotation axis. This means that the magnetic North Pole is not in the same place as the geographic North Pole, and neither of these poles is in the same place as the celestial North Pole.

A compass works because some minerals are magnetic. The needle of a compass is a magnet that aligns itself with the magnetic field of the Earth. The north pole of the needle aligns itself with the magnetic north pole.
output_2: The basic idea of a compass is that there is a magnet inside that is freely able to rotate. This magnet has a north pole and a south pole. The north pole is attracted to the Earth's magnetic north pole, and the south pole is attracted to the Earth's magnetic south pole. Because the Earth's magnetic poles are not exactly the same as the geographical poles, the needle will not point exactly north, but it will still point in a useful direction.

instruction: How do you drill ceramic tile?
output_1:
Ceramic tile is one of the most durable and attractive options for floors, walls, and countertops. However, drilling into ceramic tile is a challenge due to the material’s density and the potential for the drill to slip. If you need to drill into ceramic tile, follow these tips for the best results:

* Prepare the work area: Clear the space around the area you will be drilling to ensure safety. Remove any rugs or other items that could cause you to trip or fall. Secure any loose tiles or pieces that could be damaged by the drill.
* Choose the right drill bit: Use a carbide-tipped masonry drill bit designed for ceramic tile. These bits have sharp tips that are durable and can cut through ceramic tile without dulling. Choose a bit that is slightly smaller than the diameter of the hole you want to drill.
* Mark the hole: Use a permanent marker to draw a line around the area you want to drill. This will help you keep the drill bit centered and prevent it from slipping.
* Set up a vacuum: A wet/dry shop vac is a handy tool for keeping the work area clean while drilling into ceramic tile. Set it up near the work area and make sure it is plugged in and ready to go.
* Wet the drill bit: Dip the drill bit in water before drilling into the ceramic tile. This will keep the bit cool and help prevent it from overheating and damaging the tile.
* Position the drill: Set the drill on top of the ceramic tile and hold it firmly in place. Make sure the drill is at a 90-degree angle to the tile and the bit is centered on the marked hole.
* Start drilling: Apply slow, steady pressure to the drill as you begin drilling into the ceramic tile. Hold the drill firmly in place and keep it moving in a circular motion. Do not force the drill or apply too much pressure, as this can cause the bit to slip and damage the tile.
* Stop drilling: If the drill bit begins to slow down, stop drilling and remove it from the hole. Let the drill bit cool down and dry before continuing.
* Repeat as needed: Repeat the above steps for each hole you need to drill into the ceramic tile.

Drilling into ceramic tile is a challenging task, but with the right tools and technique, you can achieve professional-looking results. Practice on scrap pieces of tile before drilling into your actual project to ensure you have the right technique.

Always wear safety glasses or a face shield when drilling into ceramic tile, as the drill bit can fly off and cause injury. Work in a well-ventilated area and keep a wet rag handy to wipe away dust.
output_2: You’ll need a drill bit designed for ceramic tile, as well as a hammer and chisel. First, mark the spot where you want to drill, and then use the hammer and chisel to score a line in the tile. Insert the drill bit into the drill, and then hold it firmly against the tile while you apply pressure. If you’re drilling through a ceramic tile that’s less than 1/4 inch (6 mm) thick, you can simply hold the drill against the tile and apply pressure. If the tile is thicker than 1/4 inch (6 mm), you’ll want to secure it to a board or other sturdy surface before drilling.

instruction: I'd like to take in some new art. There was a cohort of Andy Warhol's called the artist Basquiat. Do you know much about the artist or his work?
output_1:
Basquiat (1960 - 1988) was a painter who emerged in the New York art scene in the early 1980s. He was born to a middle class family, but his father abandoned him and his mother soon after. He started drawing at a young age and was accepted into an art high school in Brooklyn. He struggled to make a living, however, and became a graffiti artist under the name "SAMO." Eventually he began selling his art and was able to afford an apartment and studio. He quickly rose to fame as an artist, but his success was cut short when he died of a drug overdose at age 27.

Basquiat's work often combined elements of graffiti art and fine art. His paintings were bold and energetic, featuring imagery from popular culture, such as comic books and cartoons. He also incorporated text into his paintings, which added an element of commentary to his work. Basquiat's paintings often had a strong political or social message, addressing issues such as race, poverty, and capitalism. He was one of the first artists to bring graffiti art into the mainstream, and his work has been influential on many contemporary artists.

In the 1980s, Basquiat was one of the most celebrated artists in New York. He was a frequent presence at parties and nightclubs, and he had many famous friends, including Andy Warhol. Although Basquiat died at a young age, his legacy lives on through his paintings. His work is displayed in museums around the world, and his paintings sell for millions of dollars at auction. He is considered one of the most important artists of the 20th century.

instruction: Can you give me some advice on how to be a good interviewer?
output_1:
Here are some tips that I've found helpful in interviewing:

*  Remember that you are interviewing the candidate, not the other way around.  The candidate is trying to sell you on the idea that they would be a good fit for your company.  You are trying to figure out if that is actually the case.
*  Try to be friendly, but don't overdo it.  Be polite and welcoming, but don't act too chummy.  Remember that you are still the one in charge.
*  Have a clear idea of what you're looking for in a candidate, and stick to it.  If you get off track, bring the conversation back to the point.
*  Ask open-ended questions.  "Tell me about your experience with X" is better than "Did you have much experience with X at your last job?"
*  Listen carefully to the answers.  Pay attention to what the candidate says, and ask follow-up questions if necessary.
*  Don't be afraid to ask tough questions.  You need to make sure that the candidate is qualified and a good fit for the role.  If you're not sure how to phrase a question, you can ask "Do you mind if I ask why...?"
*  Be upfront about the salary and benefits.  Don't spring this on the candidate at the end of the interview.  Let them know what they can expect from the start.
*  Be professional, but try to have some fun.  An interview should be a two-way street, not just a one-sided interrogation.
*  Send a thank-you note.  It's a small gesture that can go a long way.

Those are just a few things to keep in mind.  Remember that everyone is different, so you may need to adjust your approach depending on the situation.  Good luck!

instruction: How do I tell my kid not to lie?
output_1:
It is normal for kids to lie sometimes. As parents, we need to recognize that our child is still developing their sense of right and wrong, and that lying is one way for them to try to manage social situations and relationships.

## Recognize lying as a normal stage of development

Kids start to lie at around age 2, and continue to lie frequently throughout preschool and elementary school. Lying is a natural part of developing a conscience and learning to make moral choices.

## Do not overreact to minor lies

It is important not to overreact to a lie that is not particularly harmful or damaging. Lying is a way for children to practice moral development and to figure out what is right and wrong. Overreacting to lying can cause children to feel anxious or worried about telling the truth, which can make them less likely to tell the truth in the future.

## Deal with lying as a moral violation, not as a trust violation

It is important to distinguish between lying and trust. Lying is a moral violation, whereas breaking trust is a breach of social norms. When a child lies, we should focus on the lie itself, and not on the trust that was broken. This helps children understand that lying is wrong, regardless of whether or not they have broken trust.

## Address lying as a moral violation

When a child lies, it is important to address the lie itself, rather than the trust that was broken. For example, if a child lies about taking a toy from another child, we should focus on the lie itself, rather than on the trust that was broken by taking the toy. We can say something like, "I know you didn't take that toy. Lying is wrong. You should tell the truth next time."

## Provide clear guidance about lying

It is important to provide clear guidance to children about lying. This includes explaining why lying is wrong and what will happen if they lie. For example, we can say something like, "Lying is wrong. If you lie to me, I won't believe anything you say."

## Punish lying

It is important to punish lying, as this helps children understand that lying is wrong and helps them develop a conscience. Punishment can include removing privileges, imposing time-outs, and giving consequences. Punishment should be proportional to the lie itself. For example, lying about taking a toy from another child is less serious than lying about hurting someone.

## Help children develop a conscience

It is important to help children develop a conscience. This includes providing clear guidance about lying, punishing lying, and helping children understand why lying is wrong. It is also important to help children learn to apologize and make amends when they lie.
output_2: Telling your child not to lie is important because lying can cause serious problems for them in the short term and in the long term. In the short term, lying can lead to being found out and being in trouble. It can also damage relationships with people they lie to, because those people might not trust them again. In the long term, lying can lead to problems with the law, trouble at school, and problems in their adult lives. Telling your child not to lie is important, but it is also important to teach them why lying is wrong and to set a good example for them.

instruction: What are the differences between first, second and third degree murder?
output_1:
In the United States, there are two basic definitions of murder: first degree and second degree. In general, first degree murder is murder with premeditation (that is, with intent to kill) and second degree murder is murder without premeditation. The two most important differences between the two are that first degree murder is usually punishable by death, and second degree murder is not, and that first degree murder is usually a more serious offense in the eyes of the law.

In the United States, the various states have a large amount of leeway in how they define their murder offenses, so the exact definitions vary from state to state. Generally, first degree murder is murder with malice aforethought, which in most states is defined as premeditation and deliberation. Some states also require that the murder be committed during the commission of a felony (felony murder), or that the victim be a police officer, judge, or prosecutor (official or prosecutorial misconduct). Most states require that first degree murder be committed with premeditation, which is defined differently by each state, but generally includes situations where the defendant planned the murder in advance and deliberately carried out the plan, or when the defendant was aware that killing was a likely consequence of the acts he or she was performing and deliberately disregarded the risk of death. In some states, a first degree murder conviction requires that the defendant acted with "express malice", that is, with the intention to kill.

In some states, first degree murder is further defined into multiple subcategories, which can affect the degree of punishment or even whether the crime is punishable as a felony or a misdemeanor. For example, California has four types of first degree murder: (1) murder committed during the commission of a rape, (2) murder committed during the commission of arson, (3) murder committed during the commission of a robbery or burglary, and (4) murder committed during the commission of kidnapping. In California, if the murder is committed during the commission of one of these crimes, the defendant is punishable by life imprisonment without the possibility of parole. If the murder is not committed during the commission of one of these crimes, the defendant is punishable by either death or life imprisonment with the possibility of parole.

In most states, second degree murder is murder without premeditation or malice aforethought. Most states define second degree murder to require that the murder be committed without deliberation. In some states, second degree murder is further divided into subcategories, and is punishable by a lesser penalty. For example, in Florida, second degree murder is punishable by life imprisonment with the possibility of parole, and is defined into three subcategories: (1) felony murder, where the murder is committed during the commission of a felony, (2) felony murder by kidnaping, where the murder is committed during the commission of a kidnaping, and (3) depraved heart murder, where the defendant engages in conduct that is a gross deviation from what a reasonable person would consider acceptable in a civilized society.
output_2:
First Degree Murder

First degree murder is the most serious type of murder. It usually involves planning or malice and can be punishable by life in prison or the death penalty. Examples of first degree murder include murder for hire, murder during the commission of a felony, or murder in the course of a kidnapping.

Second Degree Murder

Second degree murder is a less serious type of murder, and is usually punishable by 10-20 years in prison. It may involve reckless behavior or lack of intent to kill, and often occurs during the commission of another crime. Examples of third degree murder include manslaughter, vehicular homicide, or killing in self-defense.

instruction: Why do I get dry skin in the winter?
output_1:
Dry skin is a common condition that affects a large portion of the population, and its prevalence is usually higher in the winter.

Dry skin is caused by a lack of moisture in the top layer of skin. This can be due to several factors, including:

* Low humidity
* Cold temperatures
* Heated indoor air
* Low water intake
* Soap
* Hot water
* Sun damage
* Medications
* Health conditions

Dry skin is often itchy, and may also be painful or flaky. It can appear on any part of the body, but is most common on the hands, feet, elbows, knees, and lower legs. Dry skin may also be red or cracked.

In the winter, dry skin is often made worse by indoor heating, which removes moisture from the air. Low humidity can also contribute to dry skin. Low temperatures outside can also cause dry skin. The cold air can make the skin dry and irritated. The air in heated buildings is often dry as well, due to forced air heating. Heated air also tends to be drier than outside air, and can cause dry skin.

Another common cause of dry skin is a lack of water. Dry air and cold temperatures can cause the skin to lose moisture. Water intake is also affected by the weather. Cold temperatures make you feel less thirsty. You may also be less likely to drink water when it's cold outside.

Soap can also cause dry skin. Soap is alkaline, while skin is acidic. When you wash with soap, the alkaline soap changes the skin's pH and causes it to lose moisture. Hot water can also cause dry skin. The hotter the water, the more it removes the skin's natural oils. This can cause dry skin.

Sun damage can also cause dry skin. The sun's ultraviolet (UV) rays can damage the skin's moisture barrier. This allows water to escape from the skin, resulting in dryness. Medications can also cause dry skin. Some medications, such as diuretics, can cause dehydration. Others, such as antidepressants, can affect the skin's oil glands. Health conditions can also cause dry skin. These include psoriasis, eczema, and diabetes.

Dry skin can be treated with moisturizers. These help replace the lost oils and water in the skin. Moisturizers can be applied topically or taken orally. Topical moisturizers are applied to the skin, while oral moisturizers are taken by mouth. Both types help to keep the skin hydrated. Topical moisturizers include lotions, creams, ointments, and oils. They work by forming a protective barrier on the skin's surface. Oral moisturizers include glycerol and fish oil. They work by increasing the body's natural production of oils.

In addition to using moisturizers, you can also improve your skin's moisture by drinking plenty of water, limiting your time in the sun, and using a humidifier. You can also use warm water instead of hot water when washing your hands and taking showers.

If you have very dry skin, you may need to see a dermatologist. Dermatologists can prescribe stronger moisturizers or other treatments for severe cases of dry skin.

In addition, when it’s cold outside, you may wash your hands more often, which also removes moisture from your skin. To help prevent dry skin in the winter, it’s important to keep your skin moisturized, especially after washing your hands, and to avoid excessively hot indoor air.

instruction: If $f(x) = \frac{3x+2}{5}$ what is the value of $\left[f^{-1}(4)\right]^{-1}$?
output_1:
The inverse of a function $f(x)$ is the function $f^{-1}(x)$ that maps all the values of $y$ for which $f(y) = x$ to $x$. The domain of $f^{-1}(x)$ is the range of $f(x)$ and the range of $f^{-1}(x)$ is the domain of $f(x)$.

Here is the function and its inverse:

$$f(x) = \frac{3x+2}{5}$$
$$f^{-1}(x) = \frac{5}{3} - 2 = 2 - \frac{5}{3}x$$

Therefore, for $f(x) = 4$, the inverse function will give us the value of $x$:
$$2 - \frac{5}{3}x = 4$$
$$2 - 4\left(\frac{5}{3}\right) = 4$$
$$- 2\left(\frac{5}{3}\right) = 4\left(\frac{5}{3}\right)$$
$$- 2\left(\frac{5}{3}\right) = - \frac{20}{3}$$
$$- 2\left(\frac{5}{3}\right) = -\frac{5\cdot3}{3}$$
$$- 2\left(\frac{5}{3}\right) = -5$$
$$\left[f^{-1}(4)\right] = -5$$

For the inverse of the inverse function, we have:
$$\left[f^{-1}(4)\right]^{-1} = \frac{3}{5}(-5) + 2 = 2$$

\begin{align*}
f^{-1}(x) &= \left\{ \begin{array}{l l}
3x+2 & \text{ if } x < 1 \\
4-x & \text{ if } x \geq 1
\end{array} \right.
\end{align*}

To find the value of $f^{-1}(4)$, we first find the value of $x$ that satisfies $f(x) = 4$.  That is, we solve $3x+2 = 4$ for $x$.  

\begin{align*}
3x+2 &= 4 \\
3x+2 &= 3x+2 \\
3x+2 &= 3x+2 \\
3x+2 &= 3x+2 \\
3x+2 &= 4 \\
\end{align*}

The only solution to the equation $3x+2=4$ is $x=1$.  So, $f^{-1}(4) = \{1\}$.  

The inverse function of $f^{-1}(x)$ is $f \circ f^{-1}$.  Therefore, we can write $f^{-1}(4) = \{1\}$.  We can find the inverse of this value by applying the function $f$ to it.  That is,

\[ f \left( f^{-1}(4) \right) = \left( f^{-1} \right) \left( 4 \right) = f \left( \{1\} \right) = \{4-1\} = \{3\}. \]

We can simplify this result by finding the value of $3^{-1}$.  We can see that the reciprocal of $3$ is $1/3$.  Therefore, $\left[f^{-1}(4)\right]^{-1} = \{1/3\}$.

instruction: What does having too much salt in your diet do to you?
output_1:
Excess salt intake can cause the following health problems:

* High blood pressure: The most common consequence of excess salt intake is high blood pressure. Blood pressure is the force of blood pushing against artery walls as the heart pumps blood through the body. Excess salt causes the body to retain water and the blood vessels to narrow. This combination raises blood pressure. About 80% of people with high blood pressure have lifestyle-related high blood pressure, also known as primary hypertension. Dietary sodium is one of the most common causes of high blood pressure.
* Kidney damage: The kidneys filter blood and remove excess fluid and waste, including sodium. When excess salt is present, the kidneys can become overloaded and fail to function properly. In addition, the kidneys must produce extra urine to get rid of the excess salt. This can lead to dehydration and other problems.
* Puffiness: The body holds on to excess salt to maintain fluid balance, which causes fluid retention and puffiness. Some people retain salt in the hands and feet, resulting in swollen fingers and toes. Others retain salt in the legs, causing the legs to swell. Puffiness in the ankles and feet is a common sign of heart disease and kidney disease.
* Stroke: Excess salt may increase the risk of stroke. Salt raises blood pressure and narrows the blood vessels, which increases the risk of blood clots. When a blood clot forms in a narrowed blood vessel, it can cause a stroke.
* Osteoporosis: Excess salt increases calcium loss through the urine, which can cause osteoporosis. The body requires calcium to maintain bone density. Insufficient calcium can lead to weak bones and osteoporosis.
* Dehydration: Salt makes the body retain water, which can cause dehydration. If too much salt is retained, the body won't have enough water to carry out its normal functions.
output_2: Too much salt in your diet can lead to high blood pressure, which in turn can lead to heart disease and strokes.  These are all serious health problems.  If you're concerned about your salt intake, you can cut back by not adding salt when you cook, and by not eating so many processed foods, which often have a lot of salt in them.

instruction: How do I improve my MPG?
output_1:
While there are several ways to increase your MPG, here are some common techniques that many people find effective.

## Change your driving habits

1. Drive smoothly. Rapid acceleration and braking both use a lot of fuel. Instead, try to anticipate traffic lights and slow down earlier to coast to a stop.
2. Avoid high speeds. A general rule is that you should drive at about 55 mph to get the best mileage.
3. Avoid excessive idling. For example, don't leave your car idling while waiting to pick up a child from school.
4. Remove excess weight. Extra weight decreases fuel economy. Make sure to remove any unnecessary items from your trunk, such as winter tires if you don't need them.

## Use your vehicle properly

1. Keep your tires properly inflated. Underinflated tires reduce fuel economy by 0.4% for every 1 psi drop in pressure.
2. Keep your engine properly tuned. A poorly tuned engine will decrease fuel economy by as much as 4%.
3. Use the right oil weight. Using the right weight of oil will improve fuel economy by 1-2%.
4. Keep your air filter clean. A clogged air filter will decrease fuel economy by 10%.

## Choose the right fuel

1. Use the right octane rating. A higher octane rating will improve fuel economy by 1%.
2. Use high-quality fuel. Premium fuels contain detergents that will help clean your engine and improve fuel economy by 1-2%.
3. Keep your fuel system clean. A dirty fuel system can decrease fuel economy by as much as 10%.
4. Use a fuel additive. Additives can help clean your engine and improve fuel economy by 1-2%.

## Consider a hybrid vehicle

Hybrid vehicles get significantly better gas mileage than non-hybrids, and will help you save money at the pump.

## Drive an electric vehicle

Electric vehicles use only energy from batteries, so they don't use any fuel at all. They're usually powered by plugging them into a wall outlet, but some can be charged by driving on solar power.
output_2: By reducing your vehicle's weight you can improve your MPG.  You can also increase the size of your tires to reduce rolling resistance.  Additionally, you can improve your driving habits to increase your MPG.  Lastly, you can consider alternative fuels to reduce your dependence on fossil fuels.

instruction: I want to learn French. How do you think I should go about it?
output_1:
Learning a language is a long-term commitment, but it is possible to learn French even if you are a complete beginner.

## Decide how you want to learn

1. Use an online course. There are many online language courses that you can use to learn French. The best thing about an online course is that you can access it from anywhere with an internet connection. This means you can learn French during your commute, while waiting in line, or even while watching TV. Some courses are completely free, while others offer a paid subscription.
2. Download an app. There are many apps you can download on your smartphone or tablet that will help you learn French. These apps are convenient because you can use them whenever you have a spare moment, such as while waiting in line or during your commute. Many of these apps are free, but there are also some that offer premium features for a fee.
3. Attend a French class. If you want to learn French in person, you can attend a language class at a local college or community center. These classes are taught by professional teachers who can help you learn the language properly. Some classes may even offer the opportunity to practice speaking with native French speakers.
4. Hire a tutor. If you want personalized attention, you can hire a French tutor. A tutor will be able to help you learn at your own pace and focus on the areas that you need the most help with. Keep in mind that hiring a tutor can be expensive, and you may need to travel to meet with them.

## Determine your learning style

1. Identify what type of learner you are. There are three main learning styles: auditory, visual, and kinesthetic. Auditory learners learn best by listening, visual learners learn best by seeing, and kinesthetic learners learn best by doing. If you're not sure what learning style you are, try taking a quiz to find out.
2. Choose activities that match your learning style. If you're an auditory learner, listen to French podcasts or audio books. If you're a visual learner, watch French movies or read children's books with pictures. If you're a kinesthetic learner, try learning French with flash cards or by practicing conversation with a native speaker.
3. Mix up your learning activities. While it's important to choose activities that match your learning style, it's also important to mix things up. This will help you learn more effectively and keep you from getting bored. For example, if you're an auditory learner, you may want to watch a French movie once a week to give your ears a break from listening.

## Practice what you've learned

1. Listen to French radio. Many French radio stations broadcast 24 hours a day, so you can listen to them whenever you want. Try tuning in to one of these stations while you're doing other things, like cooking, cleaning, or exercising.
2. Read French books. If you're a visual learner, reading books is a great way to practice your French. Start with children's books or comics, and work your way up to novels as you get more comfortable.
3. Watch French movies. Watching French movies is a great way to practice your listening and reading skills. Try watching a French movie once a week, and stop it every few minutes to look up words you don't understand.
4. Practice speaking French with a native speaker. If you have the opportunity to practice speaking French with a native speaker, take it! This will help you learn how to pronounce words correctly and pick up on nuances of the language that you won't learn from books or movies.
5. Keep a French journal. Writing in a French journal is a great way to practice your writing skills. Try writing about your day in French, or describing what you see around you.

instruction: Can you describe what light therapy can help with?
output_1:
Light therapy (also called phototherapy) is the use of light to affect mood or physiology.

* Light therapy for mood disorders.  Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD), which is depression that comes and goes with the seasons, is the best known application of light therapy. For some people who have SAD, light therapy can be as effective as medication. It can be used to treat other mood disorders, too. The theory is that light therapy changes the level of the hormone melatonin in the body, and this in turn helps to change mood.

* Light therapy for sleep disorders.  It may help people who have sleep disorders that are related to circadian rhythm disruption, such as jet lag and shift work. It may also help people with insomnia and people who have problems with sleep due to chronic pain.

* Light therapy for skin problems.  Light therapy can help to treat acne, psoriasis, and vitiligo. The theory is that light therapy helps these conditions by decreasing inflammation.

It’s used for a lot of different things, like seasonal affective disorder (SAD) and other mood disorders, jet lag, insomnia, and even acne.  The most common type is called “bright light therapy”, which involves sitting in front of a special light box for a set amount of time every day.  The light box emits bright white light, and this light helps reset your body’s internal clock and regulate your hormones.  For seasonal affective disorder, it can help relieve symptoms like depression and anxiety that come with the shorter days and darker mornings in the winter.  For jet lag, it can help you adjust to the new time zone faster by helping reset your body clock.  And for acne, it can help reduce oil production and decrease inflammation.

instruction: Simplify $(3-i)(6+2i)$.

\begin{align*}
(3-i)(6+2i) &= 3(6+2i)-i(6+2i) \\
&= 36-9i-3i \\
&= 27-3i
\end{align*}

We multiply by $i$ on both sides of the equation: \begin{align*}
(3-i)(6+2i) &= (3-i)(6) + (3-i)(2i) \\
&= 3\cdot 6 - (3)(2i) + (-3)(2i) + i(-3)(6) + i(3)(2i) \\
&= 18 - 12i - 12i + 6i + 12i \\
&= 18 - 12i \\
&= \boxed{10 - 6i}.
\end{align*}

instruction: When should you charge your Iphone?
output_1:
Here is a general guide to how long it should take your iPhone to charge, and a few tips to help speed things up:

* iPhone 4s and earlier: 4-5 hours from 0-100%
* iPhone 5 and later: 2-3 hours from 0-100%
* Battery cases: 6-12 hours to charge, depending on the size of the battery.

Note that these are estimates, and the exact time it takes to charge your battery will depend on a number of factors, including:

* How low the battery is. It takes longer to charge a battery from 0-100% than it does to go from 50% to 100%.
* The age of your battery. Older batteries don't hold a charge as well as new batteries.
* The temperature. It takes longer to charge your battery if the temperature is lower (e.g. if it's cold outside).
* Whether you're using your phone while it's charging. The more you use your phone while it's charging, the slower it will charge.

If you're in a hurry, you can try using a higher-wattage charger to speed up the process. For example, the 12W charger that comes with your iPhone 5 will charge your battery more quickly than the 5W charger that comes with older iPhones.

You can also try using an external battery pack to charge your iPhone. This is especially useful if you're traveling and don't have access to an electrical outlet.

If you're having trouble charging your battery, there are a few things you can do to troubleshoot the problem:

* Make sure the Lightning connector is securely inserted into your iPhone and the power adapter.
* Check the cable and the charging port on your iPhone for any signs of damage. If there is any damage, try cleaning the charging port with a cotton swab dipped in rubbing alcohol.
* Make sure there's no debris in the charging port. If there is, try using a paper clip to gently remove it.
* Try using a different cable and power adapter to charge your iPhone. If you're still having trouble, it's possible that your iPhone's charging port is defective.
* Try restarting your iPhone. This will force the system to reinitialize and often resolves minor charging problems.
* Try resetting the SMC (System Management Controller) on your iPhone. This will reset the power management settings on your iPhone. To do this, follow these steps:
    * Turn off your iPhone.
    * Connect your iPhone to a computer with iTunes installed.
    * Hold down the Sleep/Wake button and the Home button at the same time for at least 10 seconds.
    * After 10 seconds, release the Sleep/Wake button, but continue holding down the Home button for another 10 seconds.
    * Release the Home button and disconnect your iPhone from your computer.
    * Turn on your iPhone.

If none of these solutions work, you may need to take your iPhone to an Apple store for repair.

These tips should help you get the most out of your iPhone's battery, and make sure it charges as quickly as possible.

instruction: What is the coefficient of $x^3$ when $$24x^4 + 6x^3 + 4x^2-7x - 5$$is multiplied by $$6x^3 + 3x^2 + 3x + 4$$and the like terms are combined?
output_1:
The coefficient of $x^3$ when the two polynomials are multiplied is
$$24\cdot 6 + 6 \cdot (-3) + 4 \cdot 1 + (-7) \cdot 3 + (-5) \cdot (-3) = -22.$$

Note that the constant term is $-22\cdot 4 = -88$.

instruction: How do you cure jaundice?
output_1:
Jaundice is a symptom, not a disease. There are many diseases that can cause jaundice, including hepatitis and gallstones. Jaundice is the yellowing of the skin and eyes due to an excess of bilirubin in the blood.

## Treating jaundice due to hepatitis

1. Get plenty of rest. Jaundice can cause fatigue and sleepiness. You should get plenty of rest so that your body can focus on repairing the damaged liver cells.
2. Drink plenty of fluids. Jaundice can cause dehydration, so you should drink plenty of fluids to prevent this. Water, juices, and sports drinks are all good options.
3. Eat a balanced diet. Your body needs plenty of nutrients to repair the damaged liver cells. A balanced diet that includes plenty of fruits and vegetables is ideal. Avoid fatty or spicy foods, which can cause further damage to your liver.
4. Take your medication as prescribed. If your doctor prescribes medications, you should take them as directed. These medications can help to treat your jaundice.
5. Avoid alcohol. Alcohol can further damage your liver, so it is best to avoid it altogether.
6. Avoid medications that can cause further liver damage. Some medications can cause additional damage to the liver. Talk to your doctor about any medications that you are taking, and ask if they could be causing further damage to your liver.
7. Avoid overexertion. You should avoid strenuous exercise while you have jaundice. Exercise can cause further stress to your liver.



## Treating jaundice due to gallstones

1. Eat a low-fat diet. A low-fat diet can help to dissolve gallstones. Avoid fatty meats, fried foods, and processed foods.
2. Drink plenty of water. Water helps to flush out the gallstones. Aim for at least 8 cups (2 liters) of water per day.
3. Take over-the-counter medications. Medications such as ursodiol (Actigall) and chenodiol (Sydostat) can help to dissolve gallstones. Talk to your doctor about whether these medications are right for you.
4. Have your gallbladder removed. If your gallstones are causing significant pain, you may need to have your gallbladder removed. This will eliminate the source of the gallstones.
5. Take a bile acid sequestrant. Medications such as colestid (colestipol) and welchol (colesevelam) can help to prevent the formation of gallstones. Talk to your doctor about whether these medications are right for you.
6. Take ursodiol (Actigall). This medication can help to dissolve existing gallstones. Talk to your doctor about whether this medication is right for you.
7. Take a cholestyramine (Questran) resin. This medication binds with bile acids in the intestine, preventing them from being reabsorbed. This can help to dissolve gallstones. Talk to your doctor about whether this medication is right for you.


## Treating jaundice due to other causes

1. Get plenty of rest. Jaundice can cause fatigue and sleepiness. You should get plenty of rest so that your body can focus on repairing the damaged cells.
2. Drink plenty of fluids. Jaundice can cause dehydration, so you should drink plenty of fluids to prevent this. Water, juices, and sports drinks are all good options.
3. Eat a balanced diet. Your body needs plenty of nutrients to repair the damaged cells. A balanced diet that includes plenty of fruits and vegetables is ideal. Avoid fatty or spicy foods, which can cause further damage to your body.
4. Take your medication as prescribed. If your doctor prescribes medications, you should take them as directed. These medications can help to treat your jaundice.
5. Avoid alcohol. Alcohol can further damage your liver, so it is best to avoid it altogether.
6. Avoid medications that can cause further liver damage. Some medications can cause additional damage to the liver. Talk to your doctor about any medications that you are taking, and ask if they could be causing further damage to your liver.
7. Avoid overexertion. You should avoid strenuous exercise while you have jaundice. Exercise can cause further stress to your body.
output_2: Jaundice is a condition that causes the skin and the whites of the eyes to turn yellow due to an excess of bilirubin in the blood.  Bilirubin is a byproduct of normal red blood cell breakdown, and in healthy people the liver removes bilirubin from the blood and excretes it in the bile.  When the liver isn’t functioning properly, bilirubin builds up in the blood, causing jaundice.  In most cases, the cause of jaundice is a non-cancerous condition that can be treated by supporting liver function and giving the liver time to heal.  For some people, the best treatment is a liver transplant.

instruction: What are some signs of a healthy romantic relationship?
output_1:
Here are some signs of a healthy romantic relationship:

* The couple communicates well and openly. They are able to express their feelings and concerns without holding anything back.
* The couple supports each other. They encourage one another to pursue their goals and dreams.
* The couple respects each other. They value one another's opinions, beliefs, and decisions.
* The couple is honest with each other. They don't lie or keep secrets from one another.
* The couple has fun together. They enjoy spending time with each other and laughing together.
* The couple is supportive of each other's relationships with friends and family. They don't interfere with one another's relationships.
* The couple trusts each other. They feel safe to share their thoughts, feelings, and experiences with each other.
* The couple has a strong emotional connection. They feel close to one another and enjoy spending time together.
* The couple is committed to one another. They are committed to building a lasting relationship together.

These are just some of the signs of a healthy romantic relationship. If you are unsure whether your relationship is healthy, it's important to communicate with your partner and ask them directly.
output_2:
It’s important to remember that every relationship is unique, and there isn’t one specific formula for a healthy relationship. That said, there are certain behaviors and patterns that are generally considered signs of a healthy relationship.

Here are a few characteristics of healthy relationships, according to the National Domestic Violence Hotline:

* Honesty and trust. Partners feel comfortable being honest with one another, and they trust that their partner will be honest with them. They don’t keep secrets from each other, and they don’t suspect their partner of keeping secrets.
* Mutual respect. Partners value and respect each other, and they don’t engage in behaviors that degrade or disrespect their partner. They value each other’s opinions and feelings, and they treat their partner with kindness and consideration.
* Equality. Partners feel equal in the relationship, and they don’t engage in behaviors that reinforce power imbalances, such as controlling or dominating their partner. They share decision-making and household responsibilities equally, and they support each other’s goals and aspirations.
* Communication. Partners are open and honest with one another, and they feel comfortable sharing their thoughts and feelings. They communicate effectively, and they resolve conflicts in a healthy way. They also communicate well outside of the relationship, such as by texting or calling throughout the day to say “I love you” or just to check in.
* Shared interests. Partners share interests and activities, and they enjoy spending time together. They feel connected and supported by their partner, and they enjoy doing things together as a couple.
* Safety. Partners feel safe and secure in the relationship, both emotionally and physically. They trust that their partner will be gentle and respectful, and they feel safe to express themselves freely. They also feel safe to set boundaries and say “no” to anything that makes them uncomfortable.

instruction: What are some tips for budgeting every month?
output_1:
The following are some tips for budgeting every month:

* Plan for monthly expenses. Know how much money you will spend every month on fixed expenses like rent/mortgage, car payment, and utilities. Factor in variable expenses like groceries, gas, and clothing. Set aside money for unexpected expenses like car repairs, medical bills, or home repairs. 
* Create a realistic monthly budget. Don't overspend on non-essentials like eating out, entertainment, and new clothes. Create a savings account and contribute regularly. 
* Track your spending. Monitor your spending and identify areas where you can save money. Set spending limits on discretionary expenses like entertainment and clothing. 
* Stick to your budget. Avoid impulse purchases and unnecessary spending. Set a budget for every paycheck and stick to it. 
* Pay off debt. Prioritize paying off high-interest debt like credit cards and personal loans. Focus on paying off debt before saving for long-term goals like retirement. 
* Save for emergencies. Create an emergency fund and contribute regularly. Aim to have at least 3-6 months' worth of living expenses saved up. 
* Set financial goals. Set short-term and long-term financial goals and create a plan to achieve them. Prioritize saving for retirement and other long-term goals. 
* Review your budget regularly. Revisit your budget every month to track your progress and make adjustments.

You should also have a budget for discretionary spending, such as groceries, eating out, entertainment, and other miscellaneous expenses.  In addition, you should have a budget for savings and debt repayment.

Once you have a budget, you need to track your spending against your budget.  This can be done using a spreadsheet or a budgeting app.  You should review your budget and track your spending at least once a week, preferably on a set day, such as on Sunday nights.  You should also track your spending on a daily basis, using the app on your phone, for example.

Finally, you need to adjust your budget as needed.  For example, if you have a major expense coming up, such as a car repair or a home repair, you may need to reduce your discretionary spending for a few months in order to save up the money for the expense.  Or, if you get a raise, you may want to increase your savings or debt repayment.  It’s important to review your budget regularly and make adjustments as needed.

instruction: how do i make meatballs in the oven?
output_1:
You can bake meatballs in the oven in two ways. You can either bake them in a pan on a rack or you can bake them in a slow cooker.

## Baking meatballs in a pan on a rack

1. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. Spread a thin layer of olive oil on the bottom of a large roasting pan. You can use a baking sheet or a cookie sheet as well.
3. Arrange the meatballs in the pan. You can bake them on the rack or directly on the pan.
4. Roast them in the oven for 20 minutes.
5. Flip the meatballs over. Roast them for 20 more minutes.
6. Remove the pan from the oven and let the meatballs rest for 10 minutes.
7. Transfer them to a serving dish. You can serve them with your favorite sauce or gravy.

## Baking meatballs in a slow cooker

1. Preheat the slow cooker on high.
2. Spread a thin layer of olive oil on the bottom of a 6-quart slow cooker.
3. Arrange the meatballs in the slow cooker. You can stack them on top of each other.
4. Add 1 cup of water.
5. Cover the slow cooker and cook on high for 1 hour.
6. Turn the heat down to low and cook for 2 hours.
7. Remove the meatballs from the slow cooker and let them rest for 10 minutes.
8. Transfer them to a serving dish. You can serve them with your favorite sauce or gravy.

## Tips and variations

- Make sure to cook the meatballs in a hot oven. If the oven isn't hot enough, the outside of the meatballs will get too dark before the inside is cooked.
- You can also bake meatballs in a slow cooker. Place the meatballs in the slow cooker and cook on low for 4 hours.
- You can freeze the baked meatballs for later use. Let them cool completely and place them in a freezer-safe bag. They will keep for up to 3 months.
- You can freeze the raw meatballs before baking them. This is a good way to make meatballs in bulk and freeze them for later use.
- You can bake meatballs in a slow cooker. Add the meatballs to the slow cooker and cook on low for 4 hours.

3. Provide a detailed medical history to your doctor.

4. Get tested for lupus.

This difference may be due to genetic mutations that affect brain development and function in people with ASD.

instruction: I'd like to start growing some grapes, how should I start?
output_1:
Growing grapes is an excellent choice for home gardening. While grapevines can be temperamental, with the right conditions they can provide fruit for years.

## Select a location

1. Select a sunny location for your vine. Grapevines need a lot of sun to grow, so pick a location that gets at least 6 hours of direct sun per day.
2. Choose a location that has good air circulation. Grapes are very susceptible to fungal infections, so make sure the location you pick gets good air circulation. If your grapevine has leaves that are yellow or brown with spots, you may have a fungus problem.
3. Check the soil. Grapevines do best in loamy soil that is well drained, moist, and fertile. You can determine the type of soil in your area by checking with your local extension office. If you have poor soil, you can add compost and manure to improve its quality.
4. Plant your vine in a raised bed if you have poor soil. If the soil in your area is not ideal for growing grapes, you can build a raised bed. Choose a location that gets plenty of sun and build a raised bed at least 2 feet (0.61 m) deep. Fill the bed with compost and manure, and plant your vine in the bed.

## Choose the right grapevine

1. Choose a hardy grapevine. Grapevines come in different varieties, and some are hardier than others. Ask your local nursery for a recommendation.
2. Choose a grapevine that is suited to your climate. Some grapevines do better in warmer climates, while others do better in cooler climates.
3. Choose a grapevine that is suited to your soil. Some grapevines do better in loamy soil, while others do better in sandy soil.
4. Choose a grapevine that is suited to your area's humidity. Some grapevines do better in dry climates, while others do better in humid climates.

## Plant the vine

1. Choose a location for your grapevine. Grapevines can grow to be quite large, so make sure you have enough space for them.
2. Dig a hole that is twice as wide as the root ball and about as deep as the root ball. If you are planting a bare-root grapevine, dig a hole that is twice as wide as the roots and about 12 inches (30.5 cm) deep. If you are planting a potted grapevine, dig a hole that is as deep as the root ball.
3. Spread the roots out evenly in the hole and cover them with soil.
4. Build a small mound of soil around the vine and water it thoroughly.
5. Secure the vine to a trellis or other support structure.
6. Cover the mound with mulch.
7. Water your vine regularly. Grapevines need about 1 inch (2.54 cm) of water per week.
8. Fertilize your vine regularly. Grapevines need a lot of nutrients to produce fruit, so fertilize them regularly.

## Care for the vine

1. Prune your vine in the spring. Grapevines need to be pruned regularly to encourage new growth. Prune away any dead or diseased branches and remove any branches that cross each other.
2. Water your vine during dry spells. Grapevines need a lot of water to produce fruit, so water them regularly during dry spells.
3. Fertilize your vine in the spring and fall. Grapevines need a lot of nutrients to produce fruit, so fertilize them regularly.
4. Harvest your grapes when they are ripe. Grapes are usually ripe when they turn dark blue or purple.

## Store your grapes

1. Store your grapes in a cool place with good air circulation. Grapes are very susceptible to fungal infections, so make sure they have good air circulation.
2. Store your grapes in a single layer. Do not stack them on top of each other.
3. Use a basket or other container with a lid to store your grapes.
4. Store your grapes in the refrigerator if you won't be able to eat them within a day or two.

instruction: What is the area of the region bounded by the graph of the equation $x^2+y^2 + 3 = -4y + 6x-1$?
output_1:
The region is a hyperbola with center at $(-3, -1)$ and transverse axis $y = 3$. Thus, its area is:
$$\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \left[ 3 + \sqrt{9 + 4x^2} - x \right] \, dx = \int_{3}^{\infty} \left[ 3 + \sqrt{9 + 4x^2} - x \right] \, dx = \frac{9}{2} - 3\sqrt{10} + \sqrt{10}\log(2) \approx 10.983 \text{ units}^2$$
output_2:
We first find the equation of the line that is perpendicular bisector of the $y$-axis and symmetric about the $y$-axis.

First, we need the equation of the line through $(-1,0)$ and $(1,0)$ that is perpendicular to the $y$-axis.  Plugging in the point-slope formula, we get $y=(-1)(0)-(0)(1)=-\boxed{1}$.

Next, we need the equation of the line that is symmetric about the $y$-axis.  Letting $y=0$ gives $x^2 + 3 = -4(0)+6(0)-1 = \boxed{1}$.

Now, we have the equations $y=\boxed{-1}$ and $y=\boxed{0}$ of the lines that are perpendicular bisector of the $y$-axis and symmetric about the $y$-axis.  So the region is contained between these two lines.  To find the area, we note that the region is contained between the two circles with center $(0,0)$ and radius $\sqrt{2}$.  We also note that the area of the sector between the two lines is one-half the area of the region between the two circles, since the sector and the circle have the same central angle.  So the area is $\frac{\pi\sqrt{2}^2}{2}=\boxed{\pi}$.

instruction: A parabola $ax^2+bx+c$ contains the points $(-1,0)$, $(0,5)$, and $(5,0)$.  Find the value $100a+10b+c$.
output_1:
The given points $(-1,0)$, $(0,5)$, and $(5,0)$ lie on a parabola.  Hence, we can write
$$\begin{cases}
-1 = -a(-1)^2-b(-1)+c\\
0  =  a(0)^2+b(0)+c\\
5  =  a(5)^2+b(5)+c
\end{cases}$$
or
$$\begin{cases}
a = -1/25\\
b = -1/5\\
c = -10/25
\end{cases}$$
and the equation of the parabola is
$$100a+10b+c = 100(-1/25)+10(-1/5)-10/25 = 40-10+25 = 55.$$

instruction: What's the difference between fantasy books and high fantasy?

This also includes books that are basically "science fiction" that happened to be written before the genre of "science fiction" was formally codified, and so they are just called "fantasy."

It is usually distinguished from low fantasy, which has a more "real world" feel to it (i.e. contemporary setting, with little to no magic or fantastical elements).  In addition, high fantasy usually involves epic, larger-than-life type plots, whereas low fantasy may involve a more personal, smaller story.

So, to put it simply, fantasy books are books that have elements of the fantastic (such as magic), while high fantasy books are fantasy books with a more traditional, epic, pre-modern setting.

instruction: I have an old canvas tent. How should I care for it?
output_1:
Here are some basic tips for caring for a canvas tent:

* Clean the tent regularly. Dirt and grime can cause the fabric to deteriorate, so it's important to clean it regularly. Use a mild soap and water solution to wipe down the tent, being sure to rinse it thoroughly afterwards to remove any soap residue.
* Dry the tent thoroughly. Canvas is vulnerable to mold and mildew, so it's important to ensure that it's completely dry before storing. Allow the tent to air dry in the sun, or use a fan to speed the process.
* Store the tent properly. Once it's completely dry, fold the tent carefully and store it in a dry place. Avoid storing the tent in direct sunlight, as this can cause the fabric to fade.
* Repair any damage. If you notice any tears or holes in the canvas, repair them as soon as possible to prevent further damage. Use a heavy-duty canvas repair kit to patch the damage and ensure that your tent lasts for years to come.
* Inspect the tent before each use. Before pitching the tent, take the time to thoroughly inspect the fabric for any signs of wear and tear. This will help you catch any problems early, before they become more serious.
* Seal the tent with waterproofing. Apply a waterproofing sealant to the canvas to protect it from the elements. This will help keep the tent dry in case of a leak, and will also help extend the life of the tent.
output_2:
Canvas tents are a classic camping staple, and they can last for many years if cared for properly. Here are some tips for caring for your canvas tent:

*   Always store your tent dry. If it gets wet, allow it to dry completely before storing it.
*   If your tent gets dirty, brush off any loose dirt or debris before washing it. Never use a hose to wash your tent, as this can damage the canvas. Instead, use a soft-bristled brush and mild soap to clean the tent. Rinse the tent thoroughly with clean water, and allow it to dry completely before storing it.
*   To protect the tent from UV damage, store it in a dark, dry place when not in use.
*   If your tent gets mold or mildew, you can remove it with a mixture of 1 part bleach to 4 parts water. Apply the mixture to the affected area, and allow it to sit for 15 minutes. Rinse the tent thoroughly with clean water, and allow it to dry completely before storing it.
*   Never store your tent wet, as this can lead to mildew or mold.

By following these tips, you can keep your canvas tent in good condition for many years of camping trips!

instruction: What does 5g mean?
output_1:
5G is the fifth generation of mobile network technology. 5G networks are designed to be faster and more reliable than previous networks, allowing for faster data transfer speeds and lower latency. 5G is expected to become available to consumers in the near future, with many carriers already testing 5G networks.

One of the main advantages of 5G is its increased speed. 5G networks are designed to be significantly faster than previous networks, with theoretical download speeds of up to 20 Gbps. This speed is made possible by 5G’s use of millimeter wave (mmWave) frequencies, which have a shorter wavelength than previous networks. This allows signals to be transmitted and received at higher frequencies, resulting in faster data transfer speeds. In addition, 5G networks are designed to have lower latency, or the time it takes for data to travel from one device to another. This means that 5G networks are better suited for applications that require low latency, such as virtual reality and autonomous driving.

Another benefit of 5G is its increased capacity. 5G networks are designed to support significantly more devices than previous networks. This is made possible by 5G’s use of small cells, which are small radio transmitters that can be placed in more locations than traditional cell towers. Small cells allow carriers to increase their coverage without having to build more cell towers.

5G networks are also designed to be more energy efficient than previous networks. This is made possible by 5G’s use of spectrum sharing, which allows multiple carriers to use the same spectrum more efficiently. This reduces the amount of energy that is needed to transmit and receive data.

5G networks are expected to be deployed in major cities first, with rollout beginning in 2019 and continuing throughout the 2020s. 5G is expected to be available to consumers by 2020, with most major carriers expected to have 5G networks in place by that time.

5G networks are designed to be faster and more reliable than previous networks. While 5G networks are still in the development stage, they are expected to become available to consumers in the near future.
output_2: 5g is the next generation of cellular mobile networks. It is planned to provide higher data rates, lower latency, and greater capacity compared to previous networks. 5g is also designed to support a wide range of new use cases, such as remote surgery, self-driving cars, and the internet of things.

instruction: What are survival horror games?
output_1:
Survival horror games are a video game genre that emphasizes suspense and horror themes. They generally focus on exploration and puzzle solving as opposed to action.

The genre originated with video games such as Sweet Home (1989), Alone in the Dark (1992), Resident Evil (1996), and Silent Hill (1999).

Survival horror games often have a first-person or third-person view, and are set in dark and eerie environments. They usually feature realistic graphics and sound effects to create a sense of uneasiness.

These games typically focus on story-driven gameplay, and feature characters who are trapped in a hostile environment. Players must use stealth and strategy to navigate the game, avoiding or fighting enemies.

One of the key elements of survival horror games is that players must manage limited resources such as ammunition and health. This creates a sense of tension and uncertainty, as players must make difficult choices about when to use these resources.

Survival horror games are known for their immersive gameplay and strong storytelling. They often feature mature themes such as violence and gore.
output_2: Survival horror is a subgenre of horror video games that emphasize psychological terror, atmospheric tension, and horror, as opposed to the more action-oriented gameplay of the survival game genre. Survival horror games often feature limited ammunition, as well as an emphasis on exploring a hostile environment and avoiding confrontation with enemies, rather than fighting them head-on. The genre is also characterized by an emphasis on story and character development, often involving a group of characters trapped in a confined space and forced to confront their fears. Popular examples of survival horror games include Resident Evil, Silent Hill, and Fatal Frame.

instruction: How do I operate the zoom function on digital cameras?
output_1:
Modern digital cameras allow you to zoom in on a subject without physically moving the lens closer to the image sensor, as was done on traditional cameras. This is called optical zoom, and it allows you to zoom in farther than a camera with a fixed lens. Digital zoom, on the other hand, just enlarges the pixels in the image, so the resulting image quality is poorer.

## Use optical zoom

1.  Press the "zoom" button on the side of the camera, if it has one. Otherwise, look on the back of the camera for a rocker switch marked with a magnifying glass. Press the switch to zoom in, and press it again to zoom out. On some cameras, you may need to press the shutter button halfway to activate the zoom function. If you do not see a zoom button or rocker switch, skip this step.
2.  Press the "telephoto" or "tele" button. This is typically labeled with a T or a magnifying glass symbol, and allows you to zoom in on the subject. It is usually labeled with a "-" sign as well, and when you press it, the zoom will switch to "wide." If you do not see this button, skip this step.
3.  Use the camera's zoom ring. This is a ring around the lens on the front of the camera. To zoom in, turn the ring clockwise, and to zoom out, turn it counterclockwise.
4.  Take the picture when you're ready. Frame your subject in the viewfinder, and then press the shutter button fully to take the picture. If you have a digital camera, you can immediately review the picture to see if it's in focus and zoomed in the way you want it to be.


## Use digital zoom

1.  Press the "zoom" button on the side of the camera, if it has one. Otherwise, look on the back of the camera for a rocker switch marked with a magnifying glass. Press the switch to zoom in, and press it again to zoom out. On some cameras, you may need to press the shutter button halfway to activate the zoom function. If you do not see a zoom button or rocker switch, skip this step.
2.  Locate the "digital zoom" button on the camera. This button allows you to digitally enlarge the subject in the viewfinder. If you do not see a digital zoom button, skip this step.
3.  Press the "digital zoom" button. When you do this, a "+" sign will appear in the viewfinder, and the subject will be digitally enlarged. To zoom out, press the button again, and the "+" sign will disappear.
output_2:
Some cameras have a zoom ring around the lens, which you can twist to zoom in and out. 

On other cameras, you'll press a button and then use a control stick to zoom in and out. The control stick might be on the back of the camera, or on the front. If it's on the front, you'll see a little symbol of a telescope with an arrow pointing left or right, to show you which way to move the stick to zoom in or out.

Most digital cameras have a "wide angle" lens setting, which is useful for taking photos of large groups of people, or of big buildings. It also helps you fit more of a landscape into the photo. Some cameras have a "telephoto" lens setting, which is useful for taking close-ups of people, or for zooming in on distant objects. You'll usually find the "wide angle" and "telephoto" lens settings in the menu on your camera.

instruction: How do you do well in a job interview?
output_1:
There are several ways to prepare for a job interview and do well in it. Here are some tips:

* Research the company and the role. This will help you to understand what the company does, what the role entails, and what the company is looking for in a candidate.
* Practice answering common interview questions. You can find examples of interview questions online and practice answering them.
* Dress appropriately. Make sure your clothing is clean and pressed, and that it is appropriate for the type of job you are interviewing for.
* Arrive early. This will give you time to calm your nerves and ensure you arrive on time.
* Answer questions thoughtfully. Take a moment to consider the question before answering it.
* Stay positive. Even if you are asked a difficult question, remain positive and try to answer the question honestly.
* Thank the interviewer for their time. Send a thank you email after the interview.

*  Do your homework. Know as much as possible about the company you’re interviewing with. This will help you come off as interested and engaged, and will also help you ask informed questions. It will also help you avoid saying anything that could be considered negative about the company.
*  Dress appropriately. You want to look professional and put together. First impressions matter, and you don’t want to be remembered for the wrong reasons.
*  Practice your answers. Think through possible interview questions, and come up with thoughtful responses. Try to anticipate the kinds of questions you might be asked, and prepare for them.
*  Focus on your strengths. In an interview, it’s important to think about what you can offer the company, rather than what the company can offer you. You want to come off as motivated and eager to work.
*  Be honest. Don’t exaggerate your experience or qualifications, and don’t lie. It will probably come back to bite you, and you don’t want to start off your new job on the wrong foot.
*  Be confident. It’s important to come off as calm, confident, and professional. You want the interviewer to think that you’re the right person for the job, and that you’ll be a good fit with the team.
*  Follow up. Send a thank you note to the interviewer, and reiterate your interest in the job.
